\begin{abstract}
A number of recent studies has focused on the implications of new physics at
the Planck scale on the equilibrium of compact astrophysical objects such as
white dwarf and neutron stars. Here we analyze the modification of the
equilibrium configurations induced by the so-called Gravity's Rainbow that
account for Planck scale deformation of the space-time.

\end{abstract}

